  "text": "The Barratt Impulsiveness Scale-11 (BIS-11) was used to assess the behavioral construct of impulsiveness [CITATION_1] . The BIS-11 is composed of 30 items describing attentional, motor, and non-planning impulsivity behaviors and preferences. Items are scored on a four-point Likert scale (1 = rarely/never, 2 = occasionally, 3 = often, 4 = almost always/always). The reliability of the general scale is 0.80.",
